<h2>Content Strategy That Builds Authority Fast</h2>
<p>Publishing random articles does not build authority. Publishing a structured content library does. Google evaluates your site by topic coverage, not by individual pages.</p>
<h3>Build Topic Clusters</h3>
<p>A <a href="/blog/build-topical-authority/">topic cluster</a> groups 10 to 20 related articles around a central pillar page. The pillar targets a broad keyword. The supporting articles target specific long-tail variations. Internal links connect every supporting article back to the pillar.</p>
